    body: 'What is Zero-Copy Cloning in Snowflake and when would you use it in a data pipeline?',
    answer: 'Zero-Copy Cloning creates an instant, independent copy of a table/schema/database without duplicating underlying data — it copies only metadata pointers. Cost: you only pay for new data written to the clone after cloning. Use cases: (1) Create a dev/test environment clone of production in seconds without cost. (2) Snapshot a table before a risky transformation — rollback by querying the clone. (3) A/B test two transformation versions on the same source data. (4) Share isolated data to analysts without granting production access. Limitation: original micro-partitions are retained until all clones referencing them are dropped.',
