    answer: 'Use Dynamic Task Mapping (Airflow 2.3+). Define a @task that returns the list of file paths, then expand it: process_file.expand(file_path=get_file_list()). Airflow creates one task instance per file at runtime. Limit concurrency with max_active_tis_per_dagrun to avoid overwhelming executors. Alternative for older Airflow: use a single PythonOperator that iterates through files internally, or KubernetesPodOperator with parallel pods. Never create 10,000 static tasks in a Python loop — this bloats the DAG serialization in the metadata DB and can crash the scheduler.',
