    answer: 'Business Requirement: the what and why at the business level — "The business needs to reduce cart abandonment by 15% by simplifying checkout." Functional Requirement: what the system must do — "The system shall allow users to check out as a guest without mandatory registration." Technical Requirement: how the system implements it — "The checkout API must respond in under 200ms with 99.9% uptime; must support TLS 1.3 encryption." BAs own the first two layers. They translate business needs into functional specs and pass technical requirements to architects. Mixing these layers causes scope confusion.',
